-- Ingves gets extended mandate to serve as Basel Committee chairman
-- 
-- Mon Jun 23, 2014 05:20AM EDT
-- None



STOCKHOLM, June 23 (Reuters) - Swedish central bank governor Stefan Ingves has received an extended mandated to serve as chairman of the Basel Committee, the country's central bank said in a statement on Monday.

His extended term, which will run until June 2017, was approved by a group of governors and heads of supervision, the statement said.